### Findings

The proportion of homes which have an EPC with an energy rating of C or better has risen steadily over the last 10 years. EPC ratings measure energy efficiency and are not directly related to carbon emissions. WECA runs programmes to help homeowners understand [retrofit](https://www.retrofitwest.co.uk/) options and [businesses to reduce their carbon emissions](https://www.westofengland-ca.gov.uk/what-we-do/environment/low-carbon-business-support/).

